<subSubSection id="C37BD6A2AA321065FCED8C1FC79FFDD6" pageId="29" pageNumber="124" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDE8529AA321065FCED8C1FC79FFDD6" blockId="29.[828,1437,190,629]" pageId="29" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis id="B915593BAA321065FCED8C1FC0D2FE36" bold="true" box="[828,937,382,405]" pageId="29" pageNumber="124">Remarks.</emphasis>
This group holds some species placed previously in 
<emphasis id="B915593BAA321065FCA78CFEC08FFE15" box="[886,1012,415,438]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="124">Tenuicomus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFF0F8D8AA321065FBD58CFFC795FE16" author="CHANDLER D. S. &amp; UHMANN G. &amp; NARDI G. &amp; TELNOV D." box="[1028,1262,414,437]" pageId="29" pageNumber="124" pagination="421 - 455" refId="ref52747" refString="CHANDLER D. S., UHMANN G., NARDI G. &amp; TELNOV D. 2008: Family Anthicidae Latreille, 1819. Pp. 421 - 455. In: LOBL I. &amp; SMETANA A. (eds): Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Volume 5. Tenebrionoidea. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, 670 pp." type="book chapter" year="2008">CHANDLER et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<emphasis id="B915593BAA321065FAC88CFFC6F6FE16" box="[1305,1421,414,437]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="124">Tenuicollis</emphasis>
). They resemble members of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C61FEAAAA321065FB588CDEC67BFE76" baseAuthorityName="Chevrolat" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[1161,1280,446,470]" class="Insecta" family="Anthicidae" genus="Microhoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis id="B915593BAA321065FB588CDEC67BFE76" box="[1161,1280,446,470]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="124">M. fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C61FEAAAA321065FAE38CDEC01DFE55" authorityName="Kejval &amp; Chandler" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1898" class="Insecta" family="Anthicidae" genus="Microhoria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schimperi">
<emphasis id="B915593BAA321065FAE38CDEC01DFE55" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="124">M. schimperi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
groups based on characters of the mesoventrite and the male elytral apices, but differ by the reduced submarginal setose impressions of the metaventrite and abdominal sternum III, and by characters of the aedeagus (endophallic armature and position of the gonopore).
</paragraph>
